name: Kepler-335
scenarioDescription:
The Kepler-335 Exoplanetary System

Kepler-335 is a star with 2.3749999999999996 times the mass of the Sun, and 1.85 times its radius. It is located 4329.66 light years away from the solar system.

Kepler-335 is known to have 2 exoplanets in orbit around it.

Kepler-335 b

Kepler-335 b was discovered by the Kepler observatory using the transit method. Its discovery was announced in 2014-03. Its semi-major axis is 0.07 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. It takes 6.56 Earth days to complete an orbit around its host star, Kepler-335.

The mass of Kepler-335 b is 17.95 times the mass of Earth. The radius of Kepler-335 b is 3.39 that of Earth. At more than 10 Earth masses, Kepler-335 b is an ice giant, a planet that is made up mostly of volatiles like water, amonia and methane, and enveloped by a dense hydrogen and helium atmosphere, much like Uranus and Neptune in our solar system.

Kepler-335 c

Kepler-335 c was discovered by the Kepler observatory using the transit method. Its discovery was announced in 2014-03. Its semi-major axis is 0.36 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. It takes 67.84 Earth days to complete an orbit around its host star, Kepler-335.

The mass of Kepler-335 c is 14.22 times the mass of Earth. The radius of Kepler-335 c is 3.07 that of Earth. At more than 10 Earth masses, Kepler-335 c is an ice giant, a planet that is made up mostly of volatiles like water, amonia and methane, and enveloped by a dense hydrogen and helium atmosphere, much like Uranus and Neptune in our solar system.
description: 3D visualisation and gravity simulation of the exoplanet system Kepler-335, which contains 2 planets and was discovered by Kepler.
